WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

2
00:02:08.170 --> 00:02:10.106
Another crossing burned.

3
00:02:10.130 --> 00:02:11.673
We might never reach Tumbleton.

4
00:02:12.591 --> 00:02:15.069
So how long will it take you
to build the bloody thing again?

5
00:02:15.093 --> 00:02:18.364
We will have to find
another crossing.

6
00:02:18.388 --> 00:02:20.974
-take the long way round.
-The queen will abhor this delay.

7
00:02:22.559 --> 00:02:24.662
Lord Piper. take
100 of your fastest riders

8
00:02:24.686 --> 00:02:26.122
and make for Stoney Sept.

9
00:02:26.146 --> 00:02:27.606
Secure the barge
and transit there.

10
00:02:28.690 --> 00:02:30.627
That puts us back by a week.

11
00:02:30.651 --> 00:02:31.961
but we can do no better.

12
00:02:31.985 --> 00:02:33.921
It's our last chance
to ford the river

13
00:02:33.945 --> 00:02:35.530
with an army of this size.

14
00:02:44.414 --> 00:02:47.143
Will we
continue to suffer this Cole

15
00:02:47.167 --> 00:02:49.646
and his band of hangers-on?

16
00:02:49.670 --> 00:02:52.774
They flit about us
like fucking deer flies.

17
00:02:52.798 --> 00:02:55.818
another thing that we
do not endure in the North.

18
00:02:55.842 --> 00:02:57.552
Better deer flies
than frostbite.

19
00:02:58.804 --> 00:03:01.282
But Criston Cole
I am past enduring.

20
00:03:01.306 --> 00:03:02.784
North or South.

21
00:03:02.808 --> 00:03:06.287
Then loose my wolves
and me on the hunt.

22
00:03:06.311 --> 00:03:08.397
and we will bring him down.

23
00:03:09.815 --> 00:03:11.400
Or we could play at his game.

24
00:03:48.186 --> 00:03:49.396
Ambush!

25
00:03:54.943 --> 00:03:56.528
We're under attack!

26
00:04:00.741 --> 00:04:02.176
To the next crossing. then?

27
00:04:02.200 --> 00:04:04.011
They'll make for Stoney Sept

28
00:04:04.035 --> 00:04:05.763
and we'll once more
be ahead of them.

29
00:04:05.787 --> 00:04:08.540
Fall back!

30
00:04:44.284 --> 00:04:46.429
If I'd have known
we were expecting guests.

31
00:04:46.453 --> 00:04:48.222
I would have made up the beds.

32
00:04:48.246 --> 00:04:49.807
We're looking for
Aemond Targaryen.

33
00:04:49.831 --> 00:04:52.268
-the Kinslayer.
-Ah. yes. There's been a horde of you

34
00:04:52.292 --> 00:04:56.087
since the ungrateful queen
announced her bounty.

35
00:04:56.797 --> 00:04:59.400
Well. you won't find
your quarry here.

36
00:04:59.424 --> 00:05:01.903
There's an old man
who churns the butter.

37
00:05:01.927 --> 00:05:04.137
but he's blind in both eyes.

38
00:05:05.180 --> 00:05:08.242
And the boy
who feeds the horses.

39
00:05:08.266 --> 00:05:10.745
And then there are the ghosts.

40
00:05:10.769 --> 00:05:14.123
Seems you have not learned
the history of this place

41
00:05:14.147 --> 00:05:16.191
and the laborers who built it...

42
00:05:18.026 --> 00:05:20.862
who died here in chains...

43
00:05:21.822 --> 00:05:23.466
in service to Harren the Cruel.

44
00:05:28.620 --> 00:05:30.163
This castle breathes.

45
00:05:35.627 --> 00:05:39.214
She swallows the greedy.
the heedless.

46
00:05:42.509 --> 00:05:45.971
Her founding stones were
watered with the blood of men.

47
00:05:48.014 --> 00:05:49.975
And she's always thirsty.

48
00:06:08.577 --> 00:06:10.161
Oi! You bloody craven?!

49
00:06:12.330 --> 00:06:13.832
Fuck this place.

50
00:06:29.222 --> 00:06:30.682
Can you hear me?

51
00:06:32.767 --> 00:06:34.394
Stay back! Stay back!

52
00:06:35.520 --> 00:06:39.083
My... my brother.
Aegon. he was here.

53
00:06:39.107 --> 00:06:40.859
His face was on fire.

54
00:06:41.735 --> 00:06:43.713
I saw him.
He was clutching at me.

55
00:06:43.737 --> 00:06:46.215
dragging me down into the dark.

56
00:06:46.239 --> 00:06:49.218
-My... my brother.
-It's just the dream again. That's all.

57
00:06:54.581 --> 00:06:56.934
It's just the dream again.

58
00:07:05.884 --> 00:07:08.070
She saw it.

59
00:07:08.094 --> 00:07:12.074
She said I would die.
that I ruined everything.

60
00:07:12.098 --> 00:07:13.308
No.

61
00:07:23.109 --> 00:07:24.879
Mother.

62
00:07:55.517 --> 00:07:57.745
None may enter.
save at our queen's direction.

63
00:07:57.769 --> 00:08:01.022
It is a matter of some delicacy.

64
00:08:02.565 --> 00:08:06.111
I'm not certain how familiar you
are with disorders of the. um...

65
00:08:07.195 --> 00:08:09.590
female persuasion.

66
00:08:09.614 --> 00:08:10.699
Hm?

67
00:08:24.295 --> 00:08:28.109
I must thank you again
for your loyalty. Grand Maester.

68
00:08:28.133 --> 00:08:30.236
I flatter myself to think
that I have ever been

69
00:08:30.260 --> 00:08:32.220
a faithful servant
to Your Grace.

70
00:08:33.179 --> 00:08:35.390
More than that.
you've been a friend.

71
00:08:37.642 --> 00:08:39.227
But we have now a new queen.

72
00:08:41.146 --> 00:08:44.959
And I find myself
under some scrutiny.

73
00:08:44.983 --> 00:08:47.628
I fear I can no longer offer you

74
00:08:47.652 --> 00:08:50.131
assistance after today

75
00:08:50.155 --> 00:08:52.365
without making
the proper disclosures.

76
00:08:54.325 --> 00:08:55.493
I understand.

77
00:09:10.175 --> 00:09:11.676
I don't want it.

78
00:09:12.844 --> 00:09:13.887
You must.

79
00:09:14.929 --> 00:09:17.324
It could be a boy. Do you see?

80
00:09:17.348 --> 00:09:19.184
Aegon's heir.
a rival to Joffrey.

81
00:09:20.185 --> 00:09:21.770
To Rhaenyra herself.

82
00:09:26.858 --> 00:09:29.069
She will kill it.
She will have no choice.

83
00:09:30.570 --> 00:09:32.173
Or if she does not.
she will take it from you.

84
00:09:32.197 --> 00:09:34.592
Aemond still lives.
as far as we know.

85
00:09:34.616 --> 00:09:35.885
He's at Harrenhal.

86
00:09:35.909 --> 00:09:37.678
No. he was there.
but he has fled.

87
00:09:37.702 --> 00:09:39.913
-He's vanished.
-I have seen him.

88
00:09:41.122 --> 00:09:44.250
He burns. but without fire.

89
00:09:50.381 --> 00:09:53.194
If Aemond threatens
Rhaenyra's rule.

90
00:09:53.218 --> 00:09:55.220
she will use the child
as her shield.

91
00:09:56.554 --> 00:09:58.866
I can't do it.

92
00:09:58.890 --> 00:10:00.725
Helaena. please. Please.

93
00:10:01.893 --> 00:10:03.812
For your own sake.
do you not wish to be free?

94
00:10:04.813 --> 00:10:06.064
I can't.

95
00:10:07.565 --> 00:10:10.086
-No. No.
-Think of it. think of it as a cup of tea.

96
00:10:10.110 --> 00:10:11.712
Nothing more.

97
00:10:11.736 --> 00:10:13.380
But it isn't.

98
00:10:13.404 --> 00:10:15.633
No. No. it's not. Listen to me.

99
00:10:15.657 --> 00:10:17.051
Listen to me. it is a blessing.

100
00:10:17.075 --> 00:10:18.302
It is a remedy

101
00:10:18.326 --> 00:10:19.953
taught to the masters
of the Citadel.

102
00:10:20.954 --> 00:10:23.557
It has delivered me
from disgrace and ruin.

103
00:10:23.581 --> 00:10:26.060
It has delivered Rhaenyra
herself when she was young.

104
00:10:26.084 --> 00:10:27.669
And it will deliver you. too.

105
00:10:29.587 --> 00:10:30.981
-Helaena. Please. please.
-No.

106
00:10:31.005 --> 00:10:33.067
Listen to me.

107
00:10:33.091 --> 00:10:34.777
Will you bear a child

108
00:10:34.801 --> 00:10:38.072
who will be never more
than a hostage or a pawn?

109
00:10:38.096 --> 00:10:39.264
It's mine!

110
00:10:40.431 --> 00:10:42.350
It's my own. it's mine!

111
00:10:48.731 --> 00:10:50.835
I had hoped a seat on
the council would suffice

112
00:10:50.859 --> 00:10:52.920
as recompense for
House Frey's loyalty.

113
00:10:52.944 --> 00:10:55.131
But Harrenhal
was to be our recompense.

114
00:10:55.155 --> 00:10:57.258
payment for giving
your Winter Wolves

115
00:10:57.282 --> 00:11:00.094
passage across the Twins.
promised by your own son.

116
00:11:00.118 --> 00:11:02.471
-My son is dead.
-And now. I discover

117
00:11:02.495 --> 00:11:05.182
that you have pledged
our castle as a trophy.

118
00:11:05.206 --> 00:11:07.393
free to any hedge knight
who can bring you the head

119
00:11:07.417 --> 00:11:09.979
-of Aemond Targaryen.
-You. yourself. are welcome to try.

120
00:11:10.003 --> 00:11:12.648
Cregan Stark's army
has crossed the Trident.

121
00:11:12.672 --> 00:11:15.943
and we expect the crown's
word to be honored.

122
00:11:15.967 --> 00:11:18.612
no matter
if some grubby sell sword

123
00:11:18.636 --> 00:11:21.389
has dubbed himself Lord of
Harrenhal in the meanwhile.

124
00:11:26.644 --> 00:11:28.372
For now. however.

125
00:11:28.396 --> 00:11:31.065
I would be pleased
to join Your Grace's council.

126
00:11:37.238 --> 00:11:39.758
<i>What could anyone
possibly want in Wendish Town?</i>

127
00:11:39.782 --> 00:11:42.469
Not
Wendish Town itself. Your Grace.

128
00:11:42.493 --> 00:11:44.305
but a small village
at the outskirts.

129
00:11:44.329 --> 00:11:45.973
There were several farms burned.

130
00:11:45.997 --> 00:11:48.559
and the men we talked to were
certain it was Vhagar herself.

131
00:11:48.583 --> 00:11:51.020
The Sea Snake's
bastard. now a dragon rider.

132
00:11:51.044 --> 00:11:52.897
-That's his brother.
-Lord Darry is our ally.

133
00:11:52.921 --> 00:11:55.232
Aemond may be provoking us.

134
00:11:55.256 --> 00:11:57.568
By sacking a farm or three?
To what end?

135
00:11:57.592 --> 00:11:59.069
Dragons need to eat.

136
00:11:59.093 --> 00:12:00.654
The White Worm. she was called.

137
00:12:00.678 --> 00:12:03.073
But they are fugitives. We
will root them out soon enough.

138
00:12:03.097 --> 00:12:05.099
-The whore.
-Mm-hmm.

139
00:12:10.230 --> 00:12:12.666
There was a skirmish last
night at the Dragon Gate.

140
00:12:12.690 --> 00:12:14.251
Horses were required
to dispel it.

141
00:12:14.275 --> 00:12:15.836
If only the Lady Mysaria
had been there

142
00:12:15.860 --> 00:12:17.838
with her promised bread
and ladlefuls of stew.

143
00:12:17.862 --> 00:12:20.674
Or if. by some miracle.
the king consort's City Watch

144
00:12:20.698 --> 00:12:23.010
had shown a penny's
worth of restraint

145
00:12:23.034 --> 00:12:24.762
pursuing the pettiest of crimes.

146
00:12:24.786 --> 00:12:27.431
-the pettiest of criminals...
-Did anyone see where Vhagar flew?

147
00:12:27.455 --> 00:12:29.266
We went with all speed
to take up the trail.

148
00:12:29.290 --> 00:12:30.726
but it was two days cold.

149
00:12:30.750 --> 00:12:32.603
Once again.
Aemond is nowhere to be found.

150
00:12:32.627 --> 00:12:34.021
Two of our gold cloaks
were found dead

151
00:12:34.045 --> 00:12:36.357
in the street this morning.

152
00:12:36.381 --> 00:12:38.525
Put to the blade
by an unknown hand.

153
00:12:38.549 --> 00:12:39.693
Where was this?

154
00:12:39.717 --> 00:12:41.987
-Flea Bottom.
-Flea Bottom.

155
00:12:42.011 --> 00:12:44.031
Mm. has ever been
a realm unto itself.

156
00:12:44.055 --> 00:12:47.910
Quite ungovernable.
full of undesirables.

157
00:12:47.934 --> 00:12:51.205
Vhagar appears
while Ormund Hightower

158
00:12:51.229 --> 00:12:53.290
gathers himself at Tumbleton
to some hidden purpose.

159
00:12:53.314 --> 00:12:55.417
We need not waste our sweat
fretting over a fox

160
00:12:55.441 --> 00:12:57.211
gone to ground.
If you will not burn him...

161
00:12:57.235 --> 00:12:58.712
-He is not a f...
-then my army

162
00:12:58.736 --> 00:13:00.089
will root him out soon enough.

163
00:13:00.113 --> 00:13:02.049
As to that.
there is fresh news

164
00:13:02.073 --> 00:13:04.260
from Lord Tully's camp.

165
00:13:04.284 --> 00:13:06.220
Their march has been slowed
by interference

166
00:13:06.244 --> 00:13:08.430
from Ser Criston Cole
and his men.

167
00:13:08.454 --> 00:13:11.684
River crossings are being burned
before the army can reach them.

168
00:13:11.708 --> 00:13:13.310
Go back to the Riverlands.

169
00:13:13.334 --> 00:13:15.437
If Aemond has shown himself
once. he may do so again.

170
00:13:15.461 --> 00:13:18.232
Take no risk. but ascertain
his path. his purpose.

171
00:13:18.256 --> 00:13:19.733
If I may. Your Grace.

172
00:13:19.757 --> 00:13:22.820
We arrived back
only this morning.

173
00:13:22.844 --> 00:13:25.072
The Lady Baela has not eaten.
much less slept.

174
00:13:25.096 --> 00:13:26.907
I am more than ready to fly.

175
00:13:26.931 --> 00:13:28.575
It will not serve
us if your eyes are weary

176
00:13:28.599 --> 00:13:30.452
and your beast fatigued.

177
00:13:30.476 --> 00:13:31.936
I will send Daemon.

178
00:13:33.187 --> 00:13:36.583
I will go once I have dealt
with this business in the city.

179
00:13:36.607 --> 00:13:38.794
Our fallen soldiers.
An accounting must be made.

180
00:13:38.818 --> 00:13:41.255
-Do you not agree?
-I am able. Your Grace.

181
00:13:41.279 --> 00:13:42.965
The loss to our City Watch

182
00:13:42.989 --> 00:13:45.783
is a crime. to be sure.
but Ser Luthor will investigate.

183
00:13:46.659 --> 00:13:49.263
-It is not a matter for the crown.
-They are my men.

184
00:13:49.287 --> 00:13:51.998
And we depend on those
men now to secure your rule.

185
00:13:54.292 --> 00:13:56.544
Especially since their wages
have been withheld.

186
00:14:00.048 --> 00:14:01.549
-Your Grace.
-Not now.

187
00:14:02.967 --> 00:14:04.344
Is it always like this?

188
00:14:05.136 --> 00:14:06.697
Mm.

189
00:14:06.721 --> 00:14:07.972
Daemon.

190
00:14:10.350 --> 00:14:12.494
Have I somehow found myself
back on Dragonstone?

191
00:14:12.518 --> 00:14:14.955
That my voice must again
compete with yours?

192
00:14:14.979 --> 00:14:17.166
On the contrary. I have
pledged to fulfill your command.

193
00:14:17.190 --> 00:14:18.876
Just... later.

194
00:14:18.900 --> 00:14:21.337
I'm in no mood to jest.
What does it make of me

195
00:14:21.361 --> 00:14:23.672
if you will obey me only at a time
and place of your own choosing?

196
00:14:23.696 --> 00:14:25.466
You are the queen.

197
00:14:25.490 --> 00:14:27.301
I act in your interest.

198
00:14:27.325 --> 00:14:30.137
Good. My interest is Vhagar.

199
00:14:30.161 --> 00:14:31.680
Mine too.
But we have time enough.

200
00:14:31.704 --> 00:14:33.349
Aemond is afraid.

201
00:14:33.373 --> 00:14:34.850
He has fled
once already before you.

202
00:14:34.874 --> 00:14:37.811
-We are in no danger.
-There is treachery somewhere.

203
00:14:37.835 --> 00:14:39.480
and I seek to uncover it.

204
00:14:39.504 --> 00:14:41.815
What you seek is revenge.

205
00:14:41.839 --> 00:14:43.692
And gods know
I do not grudge you that.

206
00:14:43.716 --> 00:14:45.319
but revenge may wait.

207
00:14:45.343 --> 00:14:47.571
At this moment. there is
a disturbance in your city.

208
00:14:47.595 --> 00:14:49.847
and you. yourself.
are its likely cause.

209
00:14:52.266 --> 00:14:54.703
I did not ask Ser Luthor
to be brutal.

210
00:14:54.727 --> 00:14:57.414
You need not have
asked him anything at all.

211
00:14:57.438 --> 00:14:59.875
Will you let yourself
be rattled by vapid taunts.

212
00:14:59.899 --> 00:15:01.710
by the painting of stripes
on tavern walls?

213
00:15:01.734 --> 00:15:04.755
They are more than taunts.
They are an insult to my sons.

214
00:15:04.779 --> 00:15:06.757
A challenge
to my very legitimacy.

215
00:15:06.781 --> 00:15:08.675
You are the Queen of Dragons.

216
00:15:08.699 --> 00:15:10.844
Your strength
is your legitimacy.

217
00:15:10.868 --> 00:15:12.453
Your Grace?

218
00:15:18.709 --> 00:15:20.044
Glad news.

219
00:15:20.711 --> 00:15:23.548
Young Prince Joffrey has
returned this hour from the Vale.

220
00:15:26.467 --> 00:15:28.719
I'm told he's asked for you.

221
00:15:30.388 --> 00:15:33.200
I will come to him
when I'm able.

222
00:15:33.224 --> 00:15:34.809
I'm sure he's tired.

223
00:15:40.481 --> 00:15:42.209
It is long past
the nightingale.

224
00:15:42.233 --> 00:15:44.086
I don't care.

225
00:15:44.110 --> 00:15:45.570
Which way is West?

226
00:15:46.571 --> 00:15:47.655
I have no idea.

227
00:15:52.660 --> 00:15:55.681
-If I may say. Your Grace...
-I'm not going back.

228
00:15:55.705 --> 00:15:58.392
-We have nowhere else to go.
-You heard what I did.

229
00:15:58.416 --> 00:16:00.561
Vhagar has been sighted
at Wendish Town.

230
00:16:00.585 --> 00:16:02.563
Two days ago. Who knows
where she may be now?

231
00:16:02.587 --> 00:16:05.232
Well. Harrenhal. then. Someone
there will know something.

232
00:16:05.256 --> 00:16:07.568
Look. Aemond must have left
a... a message or a sign.

233
00:16:07.592 --> 00:16:09.695
-We can pick up his trail.
-It's 100 leagues

234
00:16:09.719 --> 00:16:11.238
to Harrenhal.
Your Grace. and the fields

235
00:16:11.262 --> 00:16:13.574
and woods are teeming
with Rivermen.

236
00:16:13.598 --> 00:16:16.452
This is more than a folly.
It is dangerous.

237
00:16:16.476 --> 00:16:19.580
Fucking seven fucking hells!

238
00:16:21.147 --> 00:16:23.750
What would you do
if you found him. hm?

239
00:16:23.774 --> 00:16:26.420
Your brother is a coiled viper.

240
00:16:26.444 --> 00:16:29.423
and you are... you are hungry.

241
00:16:29.447 --> 00:16:31.633
and broken. and spent.
and we are alone.

242
00:16:31.657 --> 00:16:33.093
If we were to be discovered...

243
00:16:33.117 --> 00:16:35.286
Stop telling me what I can't do!

244
00:16:38.623 --> 00:16:39.999
This is his fault.

245
00:16:41.209 --> 00:16:42.210
Everything.

246
00:16:43.294 --> 00:16:45.856
Every one of my miseries
is of his making.

247
00:16:45.880 --> 00:16:48.275
and I swear
before the Warrior himself.

248
00:16:48.299 --> 00:16:51.111
I'm going to find him
and fucking kill him

249
00:16:51.135 --> 00:16:52.720
or die in the attempt.

250
00:16:53.971 --> 00:16:54.972
Hm.

251
00:17:18.496 --> 00:17:19.997
You know me. I think.

252
00:17:22.333 --> 00:17:23.477
By reputation.

253
00:17:23.501 --> 00:17:25.521
It is my privilege now to listen

254
00:17:25.545 --> 00:17:28.649
to the whispers of the Red Keep.

255
00:17:28.673 --> 00:17:31.026
-The guests you receive...
-What is it that you want?

256
00:17:31.050 --> 00:17:33.844
And the gifts they bring.

257
00:17:35.763 --> 00:17:37.223
Show it to me.

258
00:17:53.364 --> 00:17:55.092
My daughter has been unwell.

259
00:17:55.116 --> 00:17:57.511
As you see. she suffers
terrible headaches.

260
00:17:57.535 --> 00:18:01.056
The maester is kind enough
to tend to her.

261
00:18:01.080 --> 00:18:03.416
And yet the flask is full.

262
00:18:08.629 --> 00:18:10.881
I took a lover after Viserys.

263
00:18:11.882 --> 00:18:13.235
The queen herself
knows the truth of it.

264
00:18:13.259 --> 00:18:15.428
I was careless. to my shame.

265
00:18:19.390 --> 00:18:21.934
It's a difficult thing.
but I should no longer delay.

266
00:18:33.988 --> 00:18:37.134
Was he a lord or a commoner?

267
00:18:37.158 --> 00:18:39.076
Or perhaps both?

268
00:18:41.912 --> 00:18:44.498
I must appeal to you.
Lady Mysaria.

269
00:18:46.250 --> 00:18:48.419
You of all people
must understand the...

270
00:18:49.587 --> 00:18:52.423
the indignities we women endure.

271
00:18:54.467 --> 00:18:56.653
There is surely no need for this
to be spoken of again.

272
00:18:56.677 --> 00:18:59.764
You would not. of course.
seek to deceive the queen.

273
00:19:02.266 --> 00:19:04.143
I am her prisoner.

274
00:19:06.270 --> 00:19:08.189
As you were once.
if I'm not mistaken.

275
00:19:14.987 --> 00:19:16.822
As you say.

276
00:19:23.537 --> 00:19:24.973
Have you ever seen the Hightower

277
00:19:24.997 --> 00:19:26.457
at Oldtown. Ser Criston?

278
00:19:27.458 --> 00:19:28.626
I've heard tell of it.

279
00:19:29.794 --> 00:19:31.796
Ormund and I had a game.

280
00:19:32.630 --> 00:19:34.006
to "run the tower."

281
00:19:35.216 --> 00:19:37.152
You'd start at the base
before dawn

282
00:19:37.176 --> 00:19:39.488
and aim to be the first one
to see the sun rise

283
00:19:39.512 --> 00:19:41.114
from the beacon.

284
00:19:41.138 --> 00:19:42.973
Of course. I let him win.

285
00:19:43.974 --> 00:19:45.810
He was a thin-skinned twat
even then.

286
00:19:46.811 --> 00:19:48.664
Mm.

287
00:19:48.688 --> 00:19:51.667
At that moment.
when the sun rises

288
00:19:51.691 --> 00:19:54.044
over the Seven Kingdoms.

289
00:19:54.068 --> 00:19:55.986
hundreds and hundreds
of miles...

290
00:19:57.697 --> 00:19:59.990
I hope to show it
to you one day.

291
00:20:01.701 --> 00:20:03.929
You could make a home
at Oldtown. Ser Criston.

292
00:20:03.953 --> 00:20:06.747
A knight of your stature
would be most welcome...

293
00:20:08.541 --> 00:20:10.167
to serve our house there.

294
00:20:16.674 --> 00:20:18.592
Halt! Stay back!

295
00:20:23.889 --> 00:20:25.599
Stay clear!

296
00:20:27.935 --> 00:20:30.015
Hold your ground!

297
00:20:31.188 --> 00:20:32.523
Stand your ground!

298
00:20:42.408 --> 00:20:44.577
Crow's feet.

299
00:20:45.786 --> 00:20:47.013
Gods.

300
00:20:47.037 --> 00:20:48.849
Are they ahead of us?

301
00:21:40.591 --> 00:21:43.236
<i>Your hand was
heavier than warranted by the crime.</i>

302
00:21:43.260 --> 00:21:46.406
I was well schooled
in those manners. was I not?

303
00:21:46.430 --> 00:21:48.182
I had the finest of captains.

304
00:21:49.642 --> 00:21:52.454
In any case.
the queen wanted it stopped.

305
00:21:52.478 --> 00:21:55.081
The queen's son is dead. She
must be excused her impulses.

306
00:21:55.105 --> 00:21:58.251
-Oh. you'd have me refuse her?
-No. rather temper her.

307
00:21:58.275 --> 00:21:59.920
Tend to her humors.
Not every whim

308
00:21:59.944 --> 00:22:01.838
needs to be pursued
with equal vigor.

309
00:22:01.862 --> 00:22:04.674
You know. they cut their bowels
as well as their throat.

310
00:22:04.698 --> 00:22:06.259
Did they tell you that?

311
00:22:06.283 --> 00:22:09.453
Good men dying in agony
in their own shit.

312
00:22:10.454 --> 00:22:12.015
We will pay the villains
back in kind.

313
00:22:12.039 --> 00:22:13.934
What is the mood among the men?

314
00:22:13.958 --> 00:22:15.936
They complain about their wages.
or lack of them.

315
00:22:15.960 --> 00:22:17.437
I shall address them.

316
00:22:17.461 --> 00:22:19.940
A rousing speech from
the Rogue Prince himself.

317
00:22:19.964 --> 00:22:22.192
I'm not sure that's gonna make
up for a steady wage anymore.

318
00:22:22.216 --> 00:22:24.110
If I lead them.
they will follow.

319
00:22:24.134 --> 00:22:26.154
It's been a minute

320
00:22:26.178 --> 00:22:28.448
since you were
the Prince of Flea Bottom.

321
00:22:28.472 --> 00:22:31.827
Most of the men were in
swaddling clothes when you...

322
00:23:32.703 --> 00:23:34.097
What is our standing?

323
00:23:34.121 --> 00:23:36.433
Battlements are being raised
with haste. my lord.

324
00:23:36.457 --> 00:23:40.896
But we lack in timber.
and men. and time.

325
00:23:40.920 --> 00:23:43.023
Then levy more conscripts.

326
00:23:43.047 --> 00:23:45.692
and fell every tree
from here to Bitter bridge.

327
00:23:45.716 --> 00:23:47.277
We must secure our walls.

328
00:23:47.301 --> 00:23:48.928
Rhaenyra's host is surely
on the march.

329
00:23:50.304 --> 00:23:53.557
The maester tells me you've been
most assiduous in your lessons.

330
00:23:55.309 --> 00:23:57.537
We are making a study
on my forebears

331
00:23:57.561 --> 00:23:59.289
on the Hightower side.

332
00:23:59.313 --> 00:24:02.876
I mean. their battles.
their enemies.

333
00:24:02.900 --> 00:24:04.920
It has been three days
now spent in the pursuit

334
00:24:04.944 --> 00:24:06.320
of these dry histories.

335
00:24:09.782 --> 00:24:11.325
Dry. did you say?

336
00:24:13.786 --> 00:24:15.579
No. Of course not.

337
00:24:18.415 --> 00:24:21.227
Or rather. they may
seem dry at first glance.

338
00:24:21.251 --> 00:24:22.795
but to learn fr...

339
00:24:24.088 --> 00:24:26.983
To venerate our ancestors.

340
00:24:27.007 --> 00:24:28.818
that is a noble task.

341
00:24:28.842 --> 00:24:30.594
And I'm grateful for it.

342
00:24:31.720 --> 00:24:33.323
Good.

343
00:24:33.347 --> 00:24:35.516
It would please me
to hear you recite.

344
00:24:39.687 --> 00:24:42.165
We have parsed out the conflicts

345
00:24:42.189 --> 00:24:46.836
between House Greyjoy
and Houses Peake

346
00:24:46.860 --> 00:24:48.922
and Osgrey and Gardener.

347
00:24:48.946 --> 00:24:50.131
House Dayne of Dorne...

348
00:24:50.155 --> 00:24:51.699
And Meria Martell?

349
00:24:53.492 --> 00:24:55.494
The Yellow Toad of Dorne.

350
00:24:58.831 --> 00:25:00.666
I should have a word
with your tutor.

351
00:25:02.292 --> 00:25:04.604
She was the only woman
ever to have been gifted

352
00:25:04.628 --> 00:25:07.006
with a truly military mind.

353
00:25:09.174 --> 00:25:12.302
Though the gods divested her
of beauty in turn.

354
00:25:13.137 --> 00:25:14.656
A blind princess.

355
00:25:14.680 --> 00:25:17.808
Hideous. hairless.
thick of waist.

356
00:25:19.393 --> 00:25:21.729
She does not sound
so formidable.

357
00:25:24.314 --> 00:25:26.334
When Aegon the Conqueror
claimed her lands.

358
00:25:26.358 --> 00:25:27.693
she refused to submit.

359
00:25:29.028 --> 00:25:30.964
She declared him a usurper.

360
00:25:30.988 --> 00:25:32.507
And all those
that marched for him.

361
00:25:32.531 --> 00:25:33.991
traitors to the Seven Kingdoms.

362
00:25:35.367 --> 00:25:38.138
And she swore that Dorne

363
00:25:38.162 --> 00:25:40.372
would ever be unbowed. unbent.

364
00:25:47.046 --> 00:25:50.191
A great host descended
from the Red Mountains.

365
00:25:50.215 --> 00:25:52.569
we Hightowers
regrettably among them.

366
00:25:52.593 --> 00:25:54.487
Meria poisoned her own wells.

367
00:25:54.511 --> 00:25:57.264
hid her soldiers
in the very sand of the desert.

368
00:25:58.390 --> 00:26:00.493
Her castle.
when they found it. was empty.

369
00:26:00.517 --> 00:26:02.996
They thought that
she was vanquished.

370
00:26:03.020 --> 00:26:04.873
But she rose up
out of the darkness

371
00:26:04.897 --> 00:26:07.066
and slaughtered them
in their beds.

372
00:26:09.276 --> 00:26:12.529
Is she a hero. then?
Or a villain?

373
00:26:19.286 --> 00:26:22.849
The Targaryens knew
nothing of our civilization.

374
00:26:22.873 --> 00:26:24.434
the Faith. the Citadel.

375
00:26:24.458 --> 00:26:26.269
What they had.

376
00:26:26.293 --> 00:26:29.755
what they still have.
is strength.

377
00:26:31.090 --> 00:26:33.550
Their armies.
the obscenity of their dragons.

378
00:26:34.259 --> 00:26:36.887
Meria Martell
outwitted her enemy.

379
00:26:37.805 --> 00:26:42.059
A cunning mind can resist
the most savage of beasts.

380
00:26:43.393 --> 00:26:46.939
And Dorne remains
unbroken even today.

381
00:27:04.832 --> 00:27:05.999
I was lucky.

382
00:27:07.334 --> 00:27:09.586
Let us start again.

383
00:27:32.317 --> 00:27:34.778
Never apologize for victory.

384
00:27:43.954 --> 00:27:45.497
I have had these made.

385
00:27:56.133 --> 00:27:57.551
Do you think it a good likeness?

386
00:28:00.137 --> 00:28:04.033
You are the sign our allies
have been waiting for.

387
00:28:04.057 --> 00:28:07.978
The son of Viserys. the beacon
shining from the High Tower.

388
00:28:09.313 --> 00:28:11.166
From the lowliest
of the faithful

389
00:28:11.190 --> 00:28:13.066
to Borros Baratheon himself.

390
00:28:19.907 --> 00:28:22.326
Oh. No. you can't touch that.

391
00:28:23.577 --> 00:28:24.828
Helaena?

392
00:28:27.164 --> 00:28:28.373
Do you know why?

393
00:28:29.333 --> 00:28:31.311
They eat the leaves
of the nightshade.

394
00:28:31.335 --> 00:28:33.188
but that would be death
for you or me.

395
00:28:33.212 --> 00:28:34.480
It's a puzzle.

396
00:28:34.504 --> 00:28:35.923
Jaehaera. come with me.

397
00:28:41.678 --> 00:28:42.930
Come.

398
00:28:47.684 --> 00:28:49.871
Listen now. dearest.
We must leave here.

399
00:28:49.895 --> 00:28:51.355
This very evening.

400
00:28:52.981 --> 00:28:54.751
There seems to be
some trouble in the city.

401
00:28:54.775 --> 00:28:58.171
and some of Rhaenyra's soldiers
must go to help the City Watch.

402
00:28:58.195 --> 00:28:59.995
We will have one guard tonight
instead of two.

403
00:29:03.951 --> 00:29:05.345
Your necklace.

404
00:29:05.369 --> 00:29:08.556
I tendered it to a maid.
She will help us.

405
00:29:08.580 --> 00:29:11.375
There is a hidden door that
leads out in Aemond's chamber.

406
00:29:12.251 --> 00:29:13.877
Below the keep
and beyond its walls.

407
00:29:14.711 --> 00:29:17.047
The one the men used
when they came to kill my boy?

408
00:29:19.216 --> 00:29:20.592
The room is Baela's now.

409
00:29:21.885 --> 00:29:23.595
And she will no doubt
be out hunting.

410
00:29:24.721 --> 00:29:26.824
With luck. we may escape

411
00:29:26.848 --> 00:29:29.118
and... and melt into the streets
of King's Landing.

412
00:29:29.142 --> 00:29:30.727
And Jaehaera?

413
00:29:32.396 --> 00:29:34.791
Her room is guarded.

414
00:29:34.815 --> 00:29:37.734
If she were to cry out.
even once...

415
00:29:38.944 --> 00:29:41.024
-then that would be the end.
-I will not leave her.

416
00:29:42.656 --> 00:29:45.760
The road ahead
will not be safe for her.

417
00:29:45.784 --> 00:29:47.720
Here. she has nursemaids
to care for her.

418
00:29:47.744 --> 00:29:50.640
and... and Rhaenyra
will... will not harm her.

419
00:29:50.664 --> 00:29:52.784
Her rivals would never
raise a girl up to rule. and...

420
00:29:53.959 --> 00:29:55.645
and it... it might be prudent.

421
00:29:55.669 --> 00:29:58.273
in fact. for the queen
to take the child to ward.

422
00:29:58.297 --> 00:30:01.675
We may even be able to...
to send for her one day.

423
00:30:08.932 --> 00:30:10.642
You look away when you lie.

424
00:30:15.439 --> 00:30:17.583
It has been days
since Vhagar was here.

425
00:30:17.607 --> 00:30:19.276
She feeds. then eludes us.

426
00:30:20.402 --> 00:30:23.447
We have traversed the Trident
50 times in the last fortnight.

427
00:30:24.656 --> 00:30:26.718
For now. we must rest.

428
00:30:26.742 --> 00:30:29.762
Could Aemond be crossing
into the Westerlands to hide?

429
00:30:29.786 --> 00:30:31.597
The Lannisters are allies.

430
00:30:31.621 --> 00:30:33.766
and there are caves and crannies
aplenty in those mountains.

431
00:30:33.790 --> 00:30:35.643
And I'll be pleased
to explore them with you

432
00:30:35.667 --> 00:30:37.770
when you've had a sleep
and a meal.

433
00:30:37.794 --> 00:30:39.314
-He may be moving by night...
-Baela!

434
00:30:42.716 --> 00:30:44.819
-My lady.
-It is well enough for you.

435
00:30:44.843 --> 00:30:46.779
The queen sees you
as her talisman.

436
00:30:46.803 --> 00:30:48.364
a sign from the gods. but I...

437
00:30:48.388 --> 00:30:49.782
It wasn't your fault.

438
00:30:49.806 --> 00:30:51.558
She won't look at me.

439
00:30:53.310 --> 00:30:54.895
And I cannot say I blame her.

440
00:30:57.064 --> 00:30:59.292
The truth is. Addam.
I wanted to go.

441
00:30:59.316 --> 00:31:01.026
I saw myself a hero.

442
00:31:02.402 --> 00:31:04.988
Turning the tide
of a great battle and...

443
00:31:06.323 --> 00:31:08.009
proving my worth to the realm.

444
00:31:08.033 --> 00:31:10.887
I have the same desire.
as do others.

445
00:31:10.911 --> 00:31:13.306
It is pride.
and I am punished for it.

446
00:31:15.040 --> 00:31:16.541
My future was ordained.

447
00:31:17.834 --> 00:31:19.252
I was one day to be queen.

448
00:31:20.170 --> 00:31:22.648
My path lay straight before me.
and now...

449
00:31:22.672 --> 00:31:24.359
Your path has vanished.

450
00:31:24.383 --> 00:31:26.176
Though it has been replaced. perhaps.

451
00:31:27.761 --> 00:31:29.155
By an adventure.

452
00:31:29.179 --> 00:31:31.866
I'll be married off.
likely enough.

453
00:31:31.890 --> 00:31:35.661
to some ancient.
self-regarding lord in Pyke.

454
00:31:35.685 --> 00:31:37.497
with enough hoarded gold
to pay Rhaenyra's debts.

455
00:31:37.521 --> 00:31:39.356
And then.
I'll come and find you.

456
00:31:40.357 --> 00:31:41.733
And we'll fly to exile.

457
00:31:43.860 --> 00:31:45.505
But only if we eat first.

458
00:31:52.035 --> 00:31:53.412
Vhagar!

459
00:31:55.205 --> 00:31:56.415
She's gone.

460
00:31:58.458 --> 00:31:59.852
No.

461
00:31:59.876 --> 00:32:02.647
No. no. she will not abandon me.

462
00:32:02.671 --> 00:32:05.066
I know only that she flew
in the night

463
00:32:05.090 --> 00:32:06.633
and I did not see where.

464
00:32:07.717 --> 00:32:09.302
Maybe she was afraid.

465
00:32:15.392 --> 00:32:16.935
Am I a prisoner?

466
00:32:49.259 --> 00:32:50.594
No.

467
00:32:55.557 --> 00:32:57.476
Without her. I'm nothing.

468
00:32:58.768 --> 00:33:01.354
-You are mistaken.
-I must find her.

469
00:33:02.814 --> 00:33:06.276
And how will you do that
if the dragon has fled?

470
00:33:08.111 --> 00:33:09.821
The queen hunts her as well.

471
00:33:12.949 --> 00:33:14.594
The queen?

472
00:33:14.618 --> 00:33:16.870
I told you.
King's Landing has fallen.

473
00:33:18.371 --> 00:33:20.624
I thought I dreamed it.

474
00:33:25.378 --> 00:33:26.505
Aegon?

475
00:33:27.380 --> 00:33:29.466
The queen says he's dead.

476
00:33:30.467 --> 00:33:31.718
And that you killed him.

477
00:33:36.181 --> 00:33:38.642
Though I do not know
how much of that to believe.

478
00:33:40.894 --> 00:33:44.397
He is dead because
he will not let me be.

479
00:33:49.694 --> 00:33:50.987
He...

480
00:33:51.821 --> 00:33:53.240
he tormented me.

481
00:33:56.409 --> 00:33:57.994
My childhood...

482
00:33:58.828 --> 00:34:00.205
I worshiped him.

483
00:34:09.172 --> 00:34:10.757
And yet our mother...

484
00:34:13.843 --> 00:34:15.178
Sometimes...

485
00:34:16.513 --> 00:34:18.348
the child that grieves her...

486
00:34:19.849 --> 00:34:21.851
is the one a mother loves best.

487
00:34:23.103 --> 00:34:24.104
Hm?

488
00:34:28.024 --> 00:34:29.359
Who are you?

489
00:34:32.028 --> 00:34:33.863
One that has been grieved.

490
00:34:42.247 --> 00:34:43.373
Go on.

491
00:34:44.291 --> 00:34:45.375
Say it.

492
00:34:48.420 --> 00:34:49.879
My dragon is dead.

493
00:34:50.797 --> 00:34:52.215
I'm a pathetic cripple.

494
00:34:53.216 --> 00:34:56.028
And there is
no possible scenario

495
00:34:56.052 --> 00:34:57.738
in which I make it
to Wendish Town

496
00:34:57.762 --> 00:34:59.740
to kill my stupid
fucking brother.

497
00:34:59.764 --> 00:35:01.242
Now as you should say.
should we...

498
00:35:01.266 --> 00:35:03.226
should we return to the camp.
Your Grace?

499
00:35:04.894 --> 00:35:07.748
I do not care to be
discovered here unguarded.

500
00:35:07.772 --> 00:35:09.208
and less so when darkness falls.

501
00:35:09.232 --> 00:35:11.544
He was Cole's little pet.
do you remember?

502
00:35:11.568 --> 00:35:13.361
A prodigy with the sword.

503
00:35:14.112 --> 00:35:16.573
Father withdrew me from
the tournaments. of course.

504
00:35:17.240 --> 00:35:20.720
Can't even remember
the pretext anymore.

505
00:35:20.744 --> 00:35:23.389
Probably just afraid
that I'd fall off my horse.

506
00:35:23.413 --> 00:35:26.392
So. I had to sit
and applaud him.

507
00:35:26.416 --> 00:35:28.251
Aemond the champion.

508
00:35:30.253 --> 00:35:32.231
And such a quick student.

509
00:35:32.255 --> 00:35:34.591
Fucking fluent in High Valyrian.

510
00:35:42.432 --> 00:35:44.577
I'm sure he thought
I was a terrible king.

511
00:35:44.601 --> 00:35:46.370
but what I could have been
if I was...

512
00:35:46.394 --> 00:35:49.582
given his fucking advantages.

513
00:35:49.606 --> 00:35:50.916
And Mother indulged him.

514
00:35:50.940 --> 00:35:52.418
She loved him more.
is the truth of it.

515
00:35:52.442 --> 00:35:55.796
Poor darling Aemond
and his scabby little eye.

516
00:35:55.820 --> 00:35:58.657
And now he's killed me. and
the whole fucking realm knows it.

517
00:36:05.455 --> 00:36:07.975
-I must say. Your Grace.
-What?

518
00:36:07.999 --> 00:36:10.460
All this time
we've been together...

519
00:36:12.796 --> 00:36:14.940
from the moment
you were injured. in fact.

520
00:36:14.964 --> 00:36:17.801
flying drunk into a battle
to which you were not invited...

521
00:36:18.677 --> 00:36:22.305
you've done nothing but whinge

522
00:36:23.473 --> 00:36:26.118
and self-flagellate
with a tenacity

523
00:36:26.142 --> 00:36:28.371
I find astonishing.

524
00:36:28.395 --> 00:36:32.124
You. who had
every advantage in life.

525
00:36:32.148 --> 00:36:36.128
You. who had every
chance to shine.

526
00:36:36.152 --> 00:36:39.131
Firstborn son.
prince of the realm.

527
00:36:39.155 --> 00:36:41.634
the finest tutors.
the finest knights

528
00:36:41.658 --> 00:36:43.284
instructing you in the sword.

529
00:36:44.202 --> 00:36:47.205
A dragon so beautiful. they
named him after the sun itself.

530
00:36:49.916 --> 00:36:52.794
You could have risen
to greatness.

531
00:36:53.670 --> 00:36:58.174
But instead. you trampled
your birthright in the mud.

532
00:37:00.927 --> 00:37:02.220
You lazed...

533
00:37:03.430 --> 00:37:05.765
reveling in mediocrity...

534
00:37:06.933 --> 00:37:09.203
fucking anything in sight
and drinking yourself

535
00:37:09.227 --> 00:37:12.021
into oblivion with
your sycophantic friends.

536
00:37:16.359 --> 00:37:17.861
I will tell you the truth.

537
00:37:19.279 --> 00:37:20.864
You were a terrible king.

538
00:37:22.615 --> 00:37:23.950
But worse than that...

539
00:37:25.034 --> 00:37:28.705
you are a terrible man.

540
00:37:44.554 --> 00:37:46.389
Don't.

541
00:37:47.640 --> 00:37:49.225
They said you were here.

542
00:37:49.893 --> 00:37:51.370
I thought there
was some mistake.

543
00:37:51.394 --> 00:37:53.205
They require of me. perhaps.

544
00:37:53.229 --> 00:37:57.126
just some show
of deference. or regard.

545
00:37:57.150 --> 00:37:59.110
-The people or the Seven?
-Both.

546
00:38:00.487 --> 00:38:02.989
There can be no harm in it.
at the least. You could try it.

547
00:38:17.420 --> 00:38:19.815
Four of my men lie dead.

548
00:38:19.839 --> 00:38:21.442
Six. if you count the two
from yesterday.

549
00:38:21.466 --> 00:38:23.802
All gold cloaks.
all killed in the same way.

550
00:38:24.677 --> 00:38:25.929
Throats cut.

551
00:40:44.776 --> 00:40:46.277
You are tired.

552
00:40:50.073 --> 00:40:51.884
You hear the wind
in these vaulted towers

553
00:40:51.908 --> 00:40:53.993
and imagine their omens
when there are none.

554
00:40:56.829 --> 00:40:58.623
Hm? These are men only.

555
00:40:59.666 --> 00:41:01.751
-Nothing more.
-Then why can't you find them?

556
00:41:30.363 --> 00:41:32.281
You are more than this.

557
00:41:36.619 --> 00:41:38.514
<i>This costs us precious time.</i>

558
00:41:38.538 --> 00:41:39.932
That is no doubt their goal.

559
00:41:39.956 --> 00:41:41.141
They knew we would
leave the road

560
00:41:41.165 --> 00:41:43.644
when we abandoned our mounts.

561
00:41:43.668 --> 00:41:46.814
This land may be theirs. but
even they could not cause thorns

562
00:41:46.838 --> 00:41:50.442
and brambles to spring
from the earth in our path.

563
00:41:50.466 --> 00:41:51.986
And men are talking
of desertion.

564
00:41:52.010 --> 00:41:54.721
Ser Criston. Friend.

565
00:41:56.472 --> 00:41:59.368
They see no sense in continuing
with this plan and to speak truth.

566
00:41:59.392 --> 00:42:01.286
nor do I. We grow weak.

567
00:42:01.310 --> 00:42:03.646
-Stoney Sept still lies far ahead.
-Mm.

568
00:42:09.318 --> 00:42:10.987
If we leave the track here...

569
00:42:11.863 --> 00:42:13.632
cut straight through the
lowlands toward the crossing.

570
00:42:13.656 --> 00:42:15.736
we may yet still gain a
day or two over Tully's host.

571
00:42:52.528 --> 00:42:54.363
Just hire the fucking ship.

572
00:43:02.205 --> 00:43:04.207
What ship might that be?

573
00:43:05.792 --> 00:43:07.376
Seven hells.

574
00:43:16.219 --> 00:43:17.859
He's gone.
My lady. be quick.

575
00:43:30.775 --> 00:43:33.879
You said the nurse
would meet us with Jaehaera.

576
00:43:33.903 --> 00:43:35.214
And so she will.
at the other end.

577
00:43:35.238 --> 00:43:37.073
-Where?
-Come. now. Quickly.

578
00:43:46.916 --> 00:43:49.293
Did you imagine
I wouldn't be watching?

579
00:43:51.212 --> 00:43:52.773
So it is she

580
00:43:52.797 --> 00:43:54.900
who is with child.

581
00:43:54.924 --> 00:43:56.735
An inconvenient heir.

582
00:43:56.759 --> 00:43:59.154
There is no need for Rhaenyra
to hear of what transpired tonight.

583
00:43:59.178 --> 00:44:02.116
I will keep no more secrets
from the queen.

584
00:44:02.140 --> 00:44:04.267
And what will be the result
if you tell her?

585
00:44:05.601 --> 00:44:07.436
We are already at her mercy.

586
00:44:08.563 --> 00:44:10.916
In but a short time. Helaena's
condition will make itself known.

587
00:44:10.940 --> 00:44:13.085
as these things
cannot help but do.

588
00:44:13.109 --> 00:44:14.819
It is not for me to decide.

589
00:44:17.196 --> 00:44:19.258
I heard tell of the White Worm.

590
00:44:19.282 --> 00:44:21.784
Years ago.

591
00:44:22.785 --> 00:44:24.596
She dealt in secrets
and extortion.

592
00:44:24.620 --> 00:44:26.205
and I knew men who feared her.

593
00:44:28.291 --> 00:44:29.768
She had the cunning
to play all sides.

594
00:44:29.792 --> 00:44:31.770
not just lapdog to the queen.

595
00:44:31.794 --> 00:44:34.982
These are rich words
in the mouth of a Hightower.

596
00:44:35.006 --> 00:44:38.551
I simply urge you
to think of yourself.

597
00:44:39.886 --> 00:44:42.138
There is good
in Rhaenyra. but...

598
00:44:43.139 --> 00:44:45.016
the crown is a weight
that crushes.

599
00:44:49.854 --> 00:44:51.707
Rhaenyra will do in the end
what she has to do.

600
00:44:51.731 --> 00:44:53.816
and what she has to do
will be dire.

601
00:44:55.443 --> 00:44:57.504
There is only one who can walk
that path with her.

602
00:44:57.528 --> 00:44:58.881
and she chose him long ago.

603
00:44:58.905 --> 00:45:00.591
She knows what Daemon is.

604
00:45:00.615 --> 00:45:03.218
They have ever been
two sides of a coin...

605
00:45:03.242 --> 00:45:04.744
as much as she may deny it.

606
00:45:07.663 --> 00:45:10.475
Her attentions
may be on you now.

607
00:45:10.499 --> 00:45:14.253
that you bathe in the warm light
of her gaze. but...

608
00:45:15.838 --> 00:45:17.399
will you stake so high a wager

609
00:45:17.423 --> 00:45:19.818
on the whims of a dragon rider?

610
00:45:19.842 --> 00:45:21.552
I want to go out.

611
00:45:23.679 --> 00:45:25.348
-Not now. dearest.
-Yes.

612
00:45:27.850 --> 00:45:29.369
I need to see the moon.

613
00:45:29.393 --> 00:45:31.187
The window will have to do.

614
00:45:32.605 --> 00:45:34.666
Speak. and you serve no one.

615
00:45:34.690 --> 00:45:36.168
you gain the queen no advantage.

616
00:45:36.192 --> 00:45:40.505
But if you say nothing.
no harm is done.

617
00:45:40.529 --> 00:45:42.615
You earn yourself favor
with the Hightowers...

618
00:45:45.618 --> 00:45:47.745
if a time should come
when you have need of it.

619
00:46:15.189 --> 00:46:17.400
He tried to stay awake
for you. Your Grace.

620
00:46:22.446 --> 00:46:25.092
Come on. keep moving!

621
00:46:25.116 --> 00:46:27.052
Keep moving now!

622
00:46:51.600 --> 00:46:53.269
Forward.

623
00:46:57.857 --> 00:47:00.818
Leave him!
Leave him where he fell.

624
00:48:12.598 --> 00:48:13.992
Where is he?

625
00:48:14.016 --> 00:48:16.018
Aemond One-Eye.
We know he's been here.

626
00:48:16.936 --> 00:48:19.063
Good ser.
this has become tiresome.

627
00:48:20.231 --> 00:48:22.709
I'm of a mind to send a message
to the queen myself.

628
00:48:22.733 --> 00:48:24.252
He's not here.

629
00:48:24.276 --> 00:48:26.505
-He has never been here.
-She's lying.

630
00:48:26.529 --> 00:48:28.757
I've heard about you. witch.

631
00:48:28.781 --> 00:48:31.367
She's no witch.
She's an imbecile.

632
00:48:32.118 --> 00:48:34.930
Cast out and wandering.
Touched in the head.

633
00:48:34.954 --> 00:48:36.681
Though not in the cunny
for too long. I think.

634
00:48:36.705 --> 00:48:38.183
Will you speak to me thus

635
00:48:38.207 --> 00:48:39.893
in the very shadow
of my fortress?

636
00:48:39.917 --> 00:48:41.770
It's been weeks
since I've had a woman.

637
00:48:41.794 --> 00:48:44.356
I'm going to fuck you
and make you my salt wife.

638
00:48:58.811 --> 00:49:00.980
Ah!

639
00:49:24.753 --> 00:49:26.755
Seems you've taken a turn
for the better.

640
00:49:36.932 --> 00:49:38.493
In Essos. we
can secrete His Grace

641
00:49:38.517 --> 00:49:40.162
until the time is right
for his return.

642
00:49:40.186 --> 00:49:43.290
But we are watched now.
We can linger here no longer.

643
00:49:43.314 --> 00:49:45.667
-You risk his safety merely by speaking...
-An ocean passage beset

644
00:49:45.691 --> 00:49:49.087
by pirates. and dragons.
and storms. and then what?

645
00:49:49.111 --> 00:49:51.423
Eating dates and incense
while Westeros

646
00:49:51.447 --> 00:49:53.925
-is reduced to ash?
-His Grace is in no state to fight.

647
00:49:53.949 --> 00:49:56.761
Neither would he tolerate
the Braavosi heat.

648
00:49:56.785 --> 00:49:59.097
-The monkeys alone...
-You surprise me. Lannister.

649
00:49:59.121 --> 00:50:00.682
Such a distaste for the foreign.

650
00:50:00.706 --> 00:50:02.225
I have lived
with these people.

651
00:50:02.249 --> 00:50:04.019
Do you forget?
I've eaten with them.

652
00:50:04.043 --> 00:50:06.403
fought with them. shared
everything with them. even their...

653
00:50:08.130 --> 00:50:09.381
Yes?

654
00:50:10.299 --> 00:50:11.634
I know what they are.

655
00:50:13.511 --> 00:50:15.780
In Braavos. I have prepared
the means for us

656
00:50:15.804 --> 00:50:17.991
to live in a manner
as befits His Grace.

657
00:50:18.015 --> 00:50:19.784
-We can ascertain...
-He is the king. Larys.

658
00:50:19.808 --> 00:50:22.787
Not some chip for you to hold
until such time as benefits you.

659
00:50:22.811 --> 00:50:25.207
-I have men riding with me...
-Sellswords.

660
00:50:25.231 --> 00:50:26.708
Cheaply bought.
by the look of them.

661
00:50:26.732 --> 00:50:28.793
We need only bring him
to Lannisport.

662
00:50:28.817 --> 00:50:30.378
where he will be sheltered.

663
00:50:30.402 --> 00:50:32.547
From there. we may summon
and command what strength

664
00:50:32.571 --> 00:50:34.508
-remains to us.
-Yes. no doubt it would be the making of the Lannisters

665
00:50:34.532 --> 00:50:36.801
to declare Casterly Rock
the new seat of the king.

666
00:50:36.825 --> 00:50:38.345
Do you think even now
of your own advancement?

667
00:50:38.369 --> 00:50:41.348
Oh. begging your pardon.
most selfless of servants.

668
00:50:41.372 --> 00:50:43.225
I was only risking my life
at sea for our common cause.

669
00:50:43.249 --> 00:50:44.976
Gregor. is it?

670
00:50:45.000 --> 00:50:47.600
It seems I missed the salient moment
when His Grace made you Hand.

671
00:50:53.050 --> 00:50:56.196
You may call me "Your Grace."

672
00:51:08.649 --> 00:51:12.045
There is an evil spirit afoot.
This is no man. I tell you.

673
00:51:12.069 --> 00:51:14.756
Do not shame yourself. Ned.
We're knights. not infants.

674
00:51:14.780 --> 00:51:17.384
But we will find these cravens

675
00:51:17.408 --> 00:51:19.010
and make a grim example of them.

676
00:51:19.034 --> 00:51:21.930
We are hunters. Not prey.

677
00:51:21.954 --> 00:51:25.016
-Hunters get paid.
-It's not safe out there!

678
00:51:27.418 --> 00:51:28.711
Enough.

679
00:51:30.045 --> 00:51:31.773
You and I are the protectors
and keepers

680
00:51:31.797 --> 00:51:34.216
of the greatest Citadel
in all of Westeros.

681
00:51:35.718 --> 00:51:37.636
The governing seat
of a mighty realm.

682
00:51:40.931 --> 00:51:44.101
Without the City Watch.
without us...

683
00:51:46.478 --> 00:51:48.678
these streets would echo
with the cries of insurrection.

684
00:51:51.066 --> 00:51:52.752
The alleys of King's Landing
would boil

685
00:51:52.776 --> 00:51:54.462
with corruption and depravity.

686
00:51:54.486 --> 00:51:57.048
I look to you now
to uphold your vows

687
00:51:57.072 --> 00:51:58.925
to the city and to the throne.

688
00:51:58.949 --> 00:52:01.052
Trust in your queen.
and I pledge you.

689
00:52:01.076 --> 00:52:03.555
you will be repaid twice over

690
00:52:03.579 --> 00:52:05.640
for the sacrifices you make now.

691
00:52:08.292 --> 00:52:09.978
And in the years to come.

692
00:52:10.002 --> 00:52:11.896
as Dorne finally
bends the knee...

693
00:52:14.089 --> 00:52:15.734
As Rhaenyra's great empire grows

694
00:52:15.758 --> 00:52:18.153
and the Seven Kingdoms
become Nine.

695
00:52:18.177 --> 00:52:21.531
become Twelve.
become the new Valyria.

696
00:52:21.555 --> 00:52:24.326
When I return with wagons

697
00:52:24.350 --> 00:52:26.244
spilling over with silks
and silver.

698
00:52:26.268 --> 00:52:29.456
who will be the first...

699
00:52:29.480 --> 00:52:31.958
to celebrate in the spoils
of conquest?

700
00:52:31.982 --> 00:52:34.336
We will!

701
00:52:34.360 --> 00:52:35.920
Groups of three and four!

702
00:52:35.944 --> 00:52:38.048
No man walks alone.

703
00:52:38.072 --> 00:52:41.593
Woodgard. Owtram.
you oversee the market square.

704
00:52:44.453 --> 00:52:45.847
It seems the Lord of Flea Bottom

705
00:52:45.871 --> 00:52:47.641
has not been
altogether forgotten.

706
00:52:47.665 --> 00:52:49.851
We've apprehended someone.
Your Grace.

707
00:52:49.875 --> 00:52:51.251
At River Row.

708
00:52:51.835 --> 00:52:53.796
Then he will be the first
to be repaid.

709
00:52:56.006 --> 00:52:57.776
Fall in!

710
00:52:57.800 --> 00:52:59.802
Stoney Sept beyond the rise!

711
00:53:21.865 --> 00:53:23.325
What is it?

712
00:53:26.495 --> 00:53:28.205
The Rivermen have crossed.

713
00:53:29.665 --> 00:53:31.250
And burned the bridge
behind them.

714
00:53:33.168 --> 00:53:35.713
We can no longer delay
their march.

715
00:53:40.884 --> 00:53:42.219
So we failed.

716
00:54:17.963 --> 00:54:19.357
How many others?

717
00:54:19.381 --> 00:54:21.049
Who was with you?

718
00:54:24.803 --> 00:54:27.139
I was the only one. I swear it.

719
00:54:28.182 --> 00:54:31.202
-I acted alone.
-Under whose instruction?

720
00:54:31.226 --> 00:54:33.538
I never saw his face.
I told you.

721
00:54:33.562 --> 00:54:35.039
The tongue or the eye?

722
00:54:38.942 --> 00:54:41.379
The eye.

723
00:54:41.403 --> 00:54:44.239
It was the king. he said!
Please!

724
00:54:46.200 --> 00:54:48.553
He said it was the king's work
I was to be about.

725
00:54:48.577 --> 00:54:49.953
It was Aegon then.

726
00:54:51.914 --> 00:54:53.165
No.

727
00:54:54.833 --> 00:54:56.418
L-Look.

728
00:54:58.670 --> 00:55:00.172
In my boot.

729
00:55:05.093 --> 00:55:08.096
Compliments of King
Daeron Targaryen. he said.

730
00:55:09.097 --> 00:55:11.934
For killing traitors
to his throne.

731
00:55:19.691 --> 00:55:21.586
No!

732
00:55:21.610 --> 00:55:23.588
No! No! Please!

733
00:55:28.534 --> 00:55:30.470
There's none who
may say that you did not give

734
00:55:30.494 --> 00:55:32.180
your best effort.

735
00:55:32.204 --> 00:55:36.124
Perhaps this is the best
we could have hoped for.

736
00:55:37.125 --> 00:55:41.189
We've made our mark
and returned alive...

737
00:55:42.965 --> 00:55:44.466
To Tumbleton. perhaps...

738
00:55:45.968 --> 00:55:47.970
to find out what Ormund
has planned.

739
00:55:50.556 --> 00:55:52.724
I thank you for your offer.
Ser Gwayne.

740
00:55:54.977 --> 00:55:56.645
But my path is set before me.

741
00:55:58.647 --> 00:56:01.984
And
what is... what is that path?

742
00:56:03.569 --> 00:56:05.195
We'll raft the river.

743
00:56:06.196 --> 00:56:08.240
Or swim it.

744
00:56:09.324 --> 00:56:11.660
It was one thing to obstruct
them. Ser Criston. but...

745
00:56:13.370 --> 00:56:15.664
you must see they've gained
the advantage.

746
00:56:17.249 --> 00:56:18.560
What more can we do?

747
00:56:18.584 --> 00:56:20.252
We will join them...

748
00:56:21.336 --> 00:56:22.880
in battle.

749
00:56:23.755 --> 00:56:25.817
Face them head on.

750
00:56:25.841 --> 00:56:27.926
We have half the men
that we set out with.

751
00:56:29.511 --> 00:56:31.722
There are 200 Rivermen
for every one of us.

752
00:56:32.764 --> 00:56:34.516
That... you...

753
00:56:35.267 --> 00:56:37.185
It would march us
towards certain death.

754
00:56:52.200 --> 00:56:55.203
This was your goal. wasn't it?

755
00:56:56.580 --> 00:56:57.789
All along.

756
00:56:58.624 --> 00:57:00.792
Our fate was always assured.
Ser Gwayne.

757
00:57:03.211 --> 00:57:05.088
When we set out.
we were doomed...

758
00:57:06.048 --> 00:57:08.067
to death and defeat.

759
00:57:08.091 --> 00:57:10.719
I have offered you sanctuary.

760
00:57:11.887 --> 00:57:13.364
Or at least the hope of one.

761
00:57:13.388 --> 00:57:15.390
You have offered me
service to your house.

762
00:57:17.935 --> 00:57:19.561
I am grateful.

763
00:57:22.356 --> 00:57:24.733
But I have... I have been
a servant all my life.

764
00:57:27.402 --> 00:57:28.987
To green or to black.

765
00:57:31.198 --> 00:57:33.492
I have defined myself
by oaths...

766
00:57:34.910 --> 00:57:36.411
through unyielding devotion.

767
00:57:37.955 --> 00:57:39.432
And the highborn
have made much of me

768
00:57:39.456 --> 00:57:40.999
while it pleased them to do so.

769
00:57:45.253 --> 00:57:47.297
But I will not let them
diminish me now.

770
00:57:50.592 --> 00:57:53.762
I will not return spurned...

771
00:57:55.347 --> 00:57:56.765
rejected.

772
00:57:59.351 --> 00:58:01.436
I am the realm's
greatest warrior.

773
00:58:04.022 --> 00:58:05.691
And I will die as such.

774
00:58:08.026 --> 00:58:09.194
Clear-eyed.

775
00:58:10.612 --> 00:58:11.697
Unbent.

776
00:58:13.490 --> 00:58:14.950
Glorious in battle.

777
00:58:17.160 --> 00:58:20.122
And not in their service. finally.

778
00:58:22.165 --> 00:58:23.375
But in my own.

779
00:58:28.130 --> 00:58:29.881
And they will sing songs of it.

780
00:58:36.013 --> 00:58:38.056
And Queen Alicent herself
will hear them.

781
00:58:46.648 --> 00:58:49.627
The plan is to rebuild
the fleet at Driftmark.

782
00:58:49.651 --> 00:58:51.629
but it will take time.

783
00:58:51.653 --> 00:58:53.488
The Velaryon resources
are diminished.

784
00:58:54.573 --> 00:58:57.176
A condition with which
I am all too familiar.

785
00:58:57.200 --> 00:58:58.886
The king consort. Your Grace.

786
00:59:00.495 --> 00:59:01.997
My prince.

787
00:59:04.791 --> 00:59:06.752
The price
of our humiliation.

788
00:59:10.005 --> 00:59:12.007
-What is this?
-Who is this.

789
00:59:13.383 --> 00:59:15.653
Young Daeron Targaryen.

790
00:59:15.677 --> 00:59:17.846
Ormund has declared him king.

791
00:59:20.265 --> 00:59:22.225
We should have burned them
when we had the chance.

792
00:59:32.402 --> 00:59:34.505
<i>We have endured much.</i>

793
00:59:34.529 --> 00:59:36.698
Suffered much.

794
00:59:37.616 --> 00:59:39.242
This I know.

795
00:59:41.578 --> 00:59:44.372
And though we languish now...

796
00:59:45.540 --> 00:59:46.750
in the darkness...

797
00:59:48.794 --> 00:59:50.772
we will not lose heart.

798
00:59:52.297 --> 00:59:54.025
Come to bed.

799
00:59:55.550 --> 00:59:56.927
She hears something.

800
01:00:02.891 --> 01:00:05.060
<i>The Seven
watch over us even now.</i>

801
01:00:11.733 --> 01:00:13.151
Look.

802
01:00:19.741 --> 01:00:21.409
<i>Let the
Maiden grant us vision.</i>

803
01:00:22.786 --> 01:00:24.621
<i>For the way ahead is blessed.</i>

804
01:00:32.671 --> 01:00:35.132
Let the Warrior
lend us his sword

805
01:00:38.593 --> 01:00:40.595
that we do not falter
in our resolve.

806
01:00:42.305 --> 01:00:43.932
And the Smith...

807
01:00:46.768 --> 01:00:48.145
Let's go.

808
01:00:49.604 --> 01:00:52.149
Let the Smith bless us
with his strength.

809
01:00:54.818 --> 01:00:56.945
<i>The Crone lights our way.</i>

810
01:00:59.281 --> 01:01:01.825
<i>Ours is the path
of righteousness.</i>

811
01:01:05.871 --> 01:01:07.038
Ser Luthor?

812
01:01:13.128 --> 01:01:14.689
Careful.

813
01:01:14.713 --> 01:01:16.506
<i>The Mother gives her comfort.</i>

814
01:01:17.674 --> 01:01:19.384
<i>The Father. his protection.</i>

815
01:01:20.802 --> 01:01:23.346
No. No. it's blocked.

816
01:01:24.472 --> 01:01:25.658
We have to go back.

817
01:01:25.682 --> 01:01:28.119
There is no way back.
the door is shut!

818
01:01:35.066 --> 01:01:37.194
No. no. no. no. no! No!

819
01:01:40.155 --> 01:01:41.698
<i>And the Stranger...</i>

820
01:02:02.219 --> 01:02:04.387
<i>The Stranger offers us rest.</i>

820
01:02:05.305 --> 01:03:05.257
